# Crypto

Constant-time symmetric primitives, written in LOGOS. The bit operations ride on
the `Word32` wrapping ring (`+` wraps mod 2³², `rotl` is a 32-bit rotation), so the
arithmetic is total and branch-free — no overflow trap, no secret-dependent path.

The ChaCha20 quarter-round (RFC 8439 §2.2.1) mixes four words of the working state
in place. `ai`/`bi`/`ci`/`di` are the zero-based positions of the four words.

The ML-KEM forward NTT (`ntt`) is the radix-2 Cooley–Tukey transform over ℤ_q, q = 3329,
computed in MONTGOMERY form. `redc(x) = x·R⁻¹ mod q` (R = 2¹⁶) reduces with a mask, two
multiplies, a shift, and a conditional subtract — NO division. Twiddles are passed in
Montgomery form (`powers[i] = wⁱ·R mod q`), so `redc(tw·x) = tw·x mod q`; the butterfly
add/sub use conditional reductions. Input is bit-reversed; output is natural order. Every
coefficient stays in [0, q), so the transform is total and the inner loop is division-free.

Native hash TOOLS Logos code calls directly (globally available, no import): `sha1(bytes)` and
`md5(bytes)` take a `Seq of Int` (bytes 0–255) and return the digest bytes; `sha3_256`/`sha3_512`/
`shake128`/`shake256` are the FIPS-202 family. `sha1` reaches an Intel **SHA-NI hardware** kernel when
the CPU has it (an order of magnitude over scalar), with a portable fallback — so a Logos algorithm
that calls `sha1` gets dedicated-silicon speed WITHOUT leaving the language. This is how `uuid.lg`'s
`uuidV5` stays both written-in-Logos and fastest: the construction is Logos, the primitive is a tool.

(NOTE for editors: keep all prose ABOVE the first `## To` — literate Logos strips only the
leading prose; a paragraph BETWEEN `## To` sections is parsed as code and breaks the module.)

## Note
The ChaCha20 quarter-round: four add-xor-rotate mixes of the state.

## To quarterRound (state: Seq of Word32) and (ai: Int) and (bi: Int) and (ci: Int) and (di: Int) -> Seq of Word32:
    Let mutable a be item (ai + 1) of state.
    Let mutable b be item (bi + 1) of state.
    Let mutable c be item (ci + 1) of state.
    Let mutable d be item (di + 1) of state.
    Set a to a + b.
    Set d to rotl(d xor a, 16).
    Set c to c + d.
    Set b to rotl(b xor c, 12).
    Set a to a + b.
    Set d to rotl(d xor a, 8).
    Set c to c + d.
    Set b to rotl(b xor c, 7).
    Set item (ai + 1) of state to a.
    Set item (bi + 1) of state to b.
    Set item (ci + 1) of state to c.
    Set item (di + 1) of state to d.
    Return state.

## Note
One 20-round ChaCha20 block: 16 keystream words from key, counter, and nonce.

## To chacha20Block (key: Seq of Word32) and (counter: Word32) and (nonce: Seq of Word32) -> Seq of Word32:
    Let mutable state be a new Seq of Word32.
    Push word32(1634760805) to state.
    Push word32(857760878) to state.
    Push word32(2036477234) to state.
    Push word32(1797285236) to state.
    Repeat for k in key:
        Push k to state.
    Push counter to state.
    Repeat for n in nonce:
        Push n to state.
    Let mutable work be a new Seq of Word32.
    Repeat for s in state:
        Push s to work.
    Repeat for r from 1 to 10:
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 0, 4, 8, 12).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 1, 5, 9, 13).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 2, 6, 10, 14).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 3, 7, 11, 15).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 0, 5, 10, 15).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 1, 6, 11, 12).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 2, 7, 8, 13).
        Set work to quarterRound(work, 3, 4, 9, 14).
    Let mutable out be a new Seq of Word32.
    Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
        Push (item i of work) + (item i of state) to out.
    Return out.

## Note
Montgomery reduction modulo the ML-KEM prime q = 3329.

## To redc (x: Int) -> Int:
    Let lo be ((x % 65536) * 3327) % 65536.
    Let t be (x + lo * 3329) / 65536.
    If t is at least 3329:
        Set t to t - 3329.
    Return t.

## Note
The number-theoretic transform over Z_q, driven by a table of twiddle powers.

## To ntt (a: Seq of Int) and (powers: Seq of Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let n be length of a.
    Let mutable len be 2.
    While len is at most n:
        Let half be len / 2.
        Let m be n / len.
        Repeat for blk from 0 to m - 1:
            Let start be blk * len.
            Repeat for j from 0 to half - 1:
                Let tw be item (m * j + 1) of powers.
                Let idx be start + j.
                Let u be item (idx + 1) of a.
                Let t be redc(tw * (item (idx + half + 1) of a)).
                Let v be u + t.
                If v is at least 3329:
                    Set v to v - 3329.
                Set item (idx + 1) of a to v.
                Let w be u - t + 3329.
                If w is at least 3329:
                    Set w to w - 3329.
                Set item (idx + half + 1) of a to w.
        Set len to len * 2.
    Return a.

## Note
Native forward NTT for ML-KEM polynomials.

## To native mlkemNtt (a: Seq of Int) -> Seq of Int

## Note
Lane-wise Montgomery multiply of two 16-lane Word16 vectors.

## To montmul (a: Lanes16Word16) and (b: Lanes16Word16) and (qv: Lanes16Word16) and (qinv: Lanes16Word16) -> Lanes16Word16:
    Let lo be a * b.
    Let t be lo * qinv.
    Let hi be mulhi16(a, b).
    Let th be mulhi16(t, qv).
    Return hi - th.

## Note
Copies 16 lanes out of a sequence starting at an offset.

## To sub16 (s: Seq of Int) and (off: Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let r be a new Seq of Int.
    Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
        Push (item (off + i) of s) to r.
    Return r.

## Note
Lane-wise Barrett reduction into canonical range mod q.

## To barrettReduce (a: Lanes16Word16) -> Lanes16Word16:
    Let h be mulhi16(a, splat16Word16(20159)).
    Let t1 be mulhi16(h + splat16Word16(512), splat16Word16(64)).
    Return a - (t1 * splat16Word16(3329)).

## Note
One butterfly level of the inverse NTT at a given stride.

## To invNttWithinLevel (coeffs: Seq of Int) and (zetas: Seq of Int) and (h: Int) and (kStart: Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let qv be splat16Word16(3329).
    Let qinv be splat16Word16(62209).
    Let mutable r be a new Seq of Int.
    Repeat for x in coeffs:
        Push x to r.
    Let blocksPerVec be 16 / (2 * h).
    Let lanesPerBlock be 2 * h.
    Repeat for v from 0 to 15:
        Let zvSeq be a new Seq of Int.
        Repeat for bj from 0 to blocksPerVec - 1:
            Let g be v * blocksPerVec + bj.
            Let zeta be item (kStart - g + 1) of zetas.
            Repeat for rep from 1 to lanesPerBlock:
                Push zeta to zvSeq.
        Let zv be lanes16Word16(zvSeq).
        Let vec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, 16 * v)).
        Let loB be nttBcastLo(vec, h).
        Let hiB be nttBcastHi(vec, h).
        Let sum be barrettReduce(loB + hiB).
        Let newHi be montmul(zv, hiB - loB, qv, qinv).
        Let rs be seqOfLanes16(nttBlend(sum, newHi, h)).
        Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
            Set item (16 * v + i) of r to (item i of rs).
    Return r.

## Note
The full inverse NTT, level by level, over 16-lane vectors.

## To invNttAllSimd (coeffs: Seq of Int) and (zetas: Seq of Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let qv be splat16Word16(3329).
    Let qinv be splat16Word16(62209).
    Let mutable r be a new Seq of Int.
    Repeat for x in coeffs:
        Push x to r.
    Set r to invNttWithinLevel(r, zetas, 2, 127).
    Set r to invNttWithinLevel(r, zetas, 4, 63).
    Set r to invNttWithinLevel(r, zetas, 8, 31).
    Let mutable kStart be 15.
    Let mutable len be 16.
    While len is at most 128:
        Let numBlocks be 128 / len.
        Let chunks be len / 16.
        Repeat for b from 0 to numBlocks - 1:
            Let zv be splat16Word16(item (kStart - b + 1) of zetas).
            Let start be b * 2 * len.
            Repeat for c from 0 to chunks - 1:
                Let lowOff be start + 16 * c.
                Let highOff be start + len + 16 * c.
                Let lowVec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, lowOff)).
                Let highVec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, highOff)).
                Let sumv be barrettReduce(lowVec + highVec).
                Let newHi be montmul(zv, highVec - lowVec, qv, qinv).
                Let nl be seqOfLanes16(sumv).
                Let nh be seqOfLanes16(newHi).
                Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
                    Set item (lowOff + i) of r to (item i of nl).
                    Set item (highOff + i) of r to (item i of nh).
        Set kStart to kStart - numBlocks.
        Set len to len * 2.
    Let fv be splat16Word16(1441).
    Repeat for v from 0 to 15:
        Let vec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, 16 * v)).
        Let scaled be seqOfLanes16(montmul(fv, vec, qv, qinv)).
        Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
            Set item (16 * v + i) of r to (item i of scaled).
    Return r.

## Note
One butterfly level of the forward NTT at a given stride.

## To nttWithinLevel (coeffs: Seq of Int) and (zetas: Seq of Int) and (h: Int) and (k0: Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let qv be splat16Word16(3329).
    Let qinv be splat16Word16(62209).
    Let mutable r be a new Seq of Int.
    Repeat for x in coeffs:
        Push x to r.
    Let blocksPerVec be 16 / (2 * h).
    Let lanesPerBlock be 2 * h.
    Repeat for v from 0 to 15:
        Let zvSeq be a new Seq of Int.
        Repeat for bj from 0 to blocksPerVec - 1:
            Let zeta be item (k0 + v * blocksPerVec + bj + 1) of zetas.
            Repeat for rep from 1 to lanesPerBlock:
                Push zeta to zvSeq.
        Let zv be lanes16Word16(zvSeq).
        Let vec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, 16 * v)).
        Let lo be nttBcastLo(vec, h).
        Let hiB be nttBcastHi(vec, h).
        Let t be montmul(zv, hiB, qv, qinv).
        Let rs be seqOfLanes16(nttBlend(lo + t, lo - t, h)).
        Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
            Set item (16 * v + i) of r to (item i of rs).
    Return r.

## Note
The full forward NTT, level by level, over 16-lane vectors.

## To nttForwardAllSimd (coeffs: Seq of Int) and (zetas: Seq of Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let qv be splat16Word16(3329).
    Let qinv be splat16Word16(62209).
    Let mutable r be a new Seq of Int.
    Repeat for x in coeffs:
        Push x to r.
    Let mutable k be 1.
    Let mutable len be 128.
    While len is at least 16:
        Let numBlocks be 128 / len.
        Let chunks be len / 16.
        Repeat for b from 0 to numBlocks - 1:
            Let zv be splat16Word16(item k of zetas).
            Let start be b * 2 * len.
            Repeat for c from 0 to chunks - 1:
                Let lowOff be start + 16 * c.
                Let highOff be start + len + 16 * c.
                Let lowVec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, lowOff)).
                Let highVec be lanes16Word16(sub16(r, highOff)).
                Let t be montmul(zv, highVec, qv, qinv).
                Let nl be seqOfLanes16(lowVec + t).
                Let nh be seqOfLanes16(lowVec - t).
                Repeat for i from 1 to 16:
                    Set item (lowOff + i) of r to (item i of nl).
                    Set item (highOff + i) of r to (item i of nh).
            Set k to k + 1.
        Set len to len / 2.
    Let mutable k0 be k - 1.
    Set r to nttWithinLevel(r, zetas, 8, k0).
    Set k0 to k0 + 16.
    Set r to nttWithinLevel(r, zetas, 4, k0).
    Set k0 to k0 + 32.
    Set r to nttWithinLevel(r, zetas, 2, k0).
    Return r.

